## Story-Level DoD

<!-- Every user story must satisfy ALL story-level DoD criteria before it can be considered done. -->

### Functional
- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified and passed
- [ ] All BDD scenarios pass automated or manual verification
- [ ] No open P1 or P2 defects on this story
- [ ] Edge cases and error paths tested
- [ ] Feature/story reviewed by Product Owner and accepted

### Code Quality
- [ ] Code reviewed by at least one peer (code review record updated)
- [ ] No critical or high findings from code review outstanding
- [ ] Code style and linting checks pass
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in code
- [ ] All TODOs resolved or tracked in backlog

### Testing
- [ ] Unit tests written and passing (coverage target met)
- [ ] Integration tests written and passing where applicable
- [ ] No regression introduced in existing tests
- [ ] Test results committed to repository

### Documentation
- [ ] API documentation updated (if applicable)
- [ ] README / inline documentation updated (if applicable)
- [ ] Architectural decisions recorded (ADR if applicable)

### AI/ML Additions (if story involves AI/ML)
- [ ] Model evaluation results documented in experiment log
- [ ] Performance thresholds from acceptance criteria met
- [ ] Bias assessment completed
- [ ] Explainability requirements satisfied
- [ ] Fallback behaviour tested and verified

## Sprint-Level DoD

<!-- The sprint is done when ALL stories meet Story-Level DoD AND all sprint-level criteria are met. -->

- [ ] All committed stories meet Story-Level DoD
- [ ] Sprint goal achieved (or formally re-scoped with Product Owner)
- [ ] Sprint review demo prepared and conducted
- [ ] Sprint retrospective held and action items recorded
- [ ] Sprint velocity recorded
- [ ] Backlog groomed for next sprint
- [ ] Risk register updated with any new or changed risks
- [ ] Assumption register updated

## Phase-Level DoD

<!-- The phase is done when all sprints complete AND phase-level evidence exists. -->

- [ ] All phase artefacts produced and in Approved or Reviewed state
- [ ] Gate review pack prepared
- [ ] Gate review conducted and outcome recorded
- [ ] All open high/critical defects resolved or accepted (with rationale)
- [ ] Evidence index updated
- [ ] Handover to next phase completed

## AI/ML Additions (Phase Level)

- [ ] Model evaluation report produced for phase
- [ ] Drift baseline established
- [ ] Data pipeline validated and documented
- [ ] Red-team or adversarial evaluation completed (if GenAI/LLM)

